# Per-page SEO checklist

Run this against the page before considering it done. Every box should be a yes.

## Crawl and index
- [ ] Route is statically rendered (or ISR), main content is in the server HTML, not client-fetched.
- [ ] Reachable from the homepage within 3 clicks via a real `<Link>`.
- [ ] Included in `sitemap.ts` with an accurate `lastModified`.
- [ ] Self-referencing canonical set via `alternates.canonical`, absolute-correct.
- [ ] No `noindex`/canonical conflict; page is not accidentally blocked in `robots.ts`.

## Metadata
- [ ] Unique title (~50-60 chars) using the template.
- [ ] Unique meta description (~140-160 chars), answer-first.
- [ ] `opengraph-image` present (1200x630) with alt.

## Structure and content
- [ ] Exactly one `<h1>`; logical `h2`/`h3` outline; semantic landmarks.
- [ ] Direct answer in the opening lines.
- [ ] Author + credentials present on content pages; `dateModified` accurate.
- [ ] Claims backed by named sources; internal links added both ways with descriptive anchors.

## Structured data
- [ ] Correct JSON-LD type for the page, server-rendered, absolute URLs, `<` escaped.
- [ ] `BreadcrumbList` on nested pages.
- [ ] Passes Google Rich Results Test and the Schema.org validator.

## Performance
- [ ] LCP image uses `next/image` with `priority`; below-fold images lazy-loaded.
- [ ] Fonts via `next/font`; third-party scripts via `next/script`, deferred/consent-gated.
- [ ] No obvious CLS source (unsized media, late-injected content).
- [ ] Spot-checked in Lighthouse against LCP < 2.5s, INP < 200ms, CLS < 0.1.
